opic of Tantra.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aTantric BuddhismzAsiavCase studies. 0aTantric Buddhism. 0aTantrismzAsiavCase studies. 0aTantrism. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology of Religion. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Ethnography. 4aAsian Studies : India and South Asian Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Tantra. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / General (see also PHILOSOPHY / Buddhist).2bisacsh1 aLorea, Carola Erika, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSingh, Rohit, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849485240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438494852423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438494852/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles